2=<span style=\"color:red;\">'''SmartRider Free Transit Zone'''</span>}}\n| services_collapsible = 1\n}}\n\n'''McIver railway station''' is a railway station on the [[Transperth Trains|Transperth]] network in [[Perth]], [[Western Australia]]. It is located on the [[Armadale and Thornlie railway lines|Armadale/Thornlie line]] and the [[Midland railway line|Midland line]], 0.9 kilometres from [[Perth railway station|Perth station]], providing access to [[Royal Perth Hospital]].\n\n==History==\nThe station was opened on 1 September 1989 and named after [[Ken McIver]], a long serving steam engine driver and [[Australian Labor Party|Labor]] member of the [[Western Australian Legislative Assembly]] for [[Electoral district of Northam|Northam]] and [[Electoral district of Avon|Avon]] from 1968 until 1986. The station was purpose-built to provide access directly to Royal Perth Hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.righttrack.wa.gov.au/Portals/3/media/History_Midland.pdf |title=History of Station on the Midland Line |accessdate=2008-03-29 |format=pdf |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080721030410/http://www.righttrack.wa.gov.au/Portals/3/media/History_Midland.pdf |archivedate=July 21, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n==Platforms==\nMcIver station is one of the two stations that service both the [[Midland railway line|Midland]] and [[Armadale railway line|Armadale/Thornlie]] lines, with the other station being [[Claisebrook railway station|Claisebrook]].\n\nThe current platforms are in use at McIver:\n{{tst|top|caption=[2777] McIver station platforms}}\n{{tst\n|stop=99011 |platform=1\n|line=[[Armadale/Thornlie railway line|Armadale/Thornlie]]\n|pattern=All stations\n|dest=[[Perth railway station|Perth]]\n|notes=}}\n{{tst\n|stop=99012 |platform=2 |pspan=2\n|line=[[Armadale/Thornlie railway line|Armadale]]\n|pattern=All stations, AB, B, C, CP\n|dest=[[Armadale railway station, Perth|Armadale]]\n|notes=}}\n{{tst\n|line=[[Armadale/Thornlie railway line|Thornlie]]\n|pattern=T\n|dest=[[Thornlie railway station|Thornlie]]\n|notes=}}\n{{tst\n|stop=99013 |platform=3\n|line=[[Midland railway line|Midland]]\n|pattern=All stations\n|dest=[[Perth railway station|Perth]]\n|notes=}}\n{{tst\n|stop=99014 |platform=4\n|line=[[Midland railway line|Midland]]\n|pattern=All stations, A, B, P\n|dest=[[Midland railway station, Perth|Midland]]\n|notes=}}\n{{tst|bottom}}\n\n==Bus routes==\n{{brt|top}}\n{{brt|stop=[12907] Wellington Street {{small|Eastbound Yellow CAT}}\n|route=3 [[Yellow CAT (Perth)|Yellow CAT]]\n|dest=to East Perth via Wellington Street<ref name=\"YellowCAT\">{{Cite Transperth bus|Perth CAT|Yellow CAT}}</ref>}}\n{{brt|stop=[12906] Wellington Street {{small|Eastbound}}|sspan=4\n|route=28\n|dest=to [[WACA Ground|WACA]] East Perth<ref name=\"Route28\">{{Cite Transperth bus|28}}</ref>}}\n{{brt|route=905\n|dest=Rail replacement service to Midland}}\n{{brt|route=907\n|dest=Rail replacement service to Armadale}}\n{{brt|route=908\n|dest=Rail replacement service to Thornlie}}\n{{brt|stop=[12920] Wellington Street {{small|Westbound Yellow CAT}} |sspan=2\n|route=3 [[Yellow CAT (Perth)|Yellow CAT]]\n|dest=to West Perth via Wellington Street<ref name=\"YellowCAT\"/>}}\n{{brt|route=28\n|dest=[[Claremont railway station, Perth|Claremont Station]] via [[HBF Stadium]]<ref name=\"Route28\" />}}\n{{brt|stop=[12921] Wellington Street {{small|Westbound}}\n|route=905, 908, 908\n|dest=Rail replacement service to Perth}}\n{{brt|bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*McIver railway station is at coordinates {{coord|-31.951743|115.866542|type:railwaystation_region:AU-WA|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n\n{{Public Transport Authority of Western Australia railway stations|Midland=y|Armadale=y|Thornlie=y|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maciver railway station, Perth}}\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1989]]\n[[Category:1989 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Perth, Western Australia]]\n", "text_old":